---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Bio, career arc, and how to reach Joao V. Rocha — AV engineer at Sound Image / Clair Global, full-stack developer, Latin Grammy nominee."
  channel="06"
  channelLabel="ABOUT"
  channelColor="white"
>
  <section class="container">
    <header class="page-head">
      <h1>Joao V. Rocha.</h1>

      <p class="lede">
        Decade behind the desk. A1 in São Paulo, A2 at Rock in Rio, now AV at
        Sound Image / Clair Global for clients like Apple and Dolby.
      </p>
      <p class="lede">
        Builds the software and hardware the operations floor is missing.
      </p>

      <nav class="jump-nav" aria-label="On this page">
        <a href="#arc">ARC</a>
        <a href="#now">NOW</a>
        <a href="#hire">HIRE</a>
        <a href="#credentials">CREDENTIALS</a>
        <a href="#community">COMMUNITY</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <figure class="portrait" aria-label="Portrait of Joao V. Rocha">
      <picture>
        <source type="image/webp" srcset="/images/me/victor-unasp-600.webp 600w, /images/me/victor-unasp-1200.webp 1200w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 480px, 100vw" />
        <img src="/images/me/victor-unasp-600.jpg" srcset="/images/me/victor-unasp-600.jpg 600w, /images/me/victor-unasp-1200.jpg 1200w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 480px, 100vw" alt="Portrait of Joao V. Rocha in headphones at the monitor position, UNASP." width="600" height="1066" loading="eager" decoding="async" />
      </picture>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <figure class="photo full-bleed">
    <picture>
      <source type="image/webp" srcset="/images/live/vmixer-birds-eye-1200.webp 1200w, /images/live/vmixer-birds-eye-1600.webp 1600w" sizes="100vw" />
      <img src="/images/live/vmixer-birds-eye-1200.jpg" srcset="/images/live/vmixer-birds-eye-1200.jpg 1200w, /images/live/vmixer-birds-eye-1600.jpg 1600w" sizes="100vw" alt="Bird's-eye view of Victor at an Allen & Heath iLive-R72, both hands on the console (touchscreen and faders); a second engineer leans in." width="1600" height="1067" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
    </picture>
    <figcaption><span class="fig">FIG. 03 ·</span> FOH POSITION · SÃO PAULO · 2017 · ALLEN &amp; HEATH iLIVE-R72</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <article class="about-body">
    <h2 id="arc">
      <span class="h2-tag">§ 01</span>
      <span class="h2-text">The short career arc.</span>
    </h2>

    <dl class="arc">
      <div class="arc-row">
        <dt>2025 — PRESENT</dt>
        <dd>AV engineer, Sound Image / Clair Global, San Francisco.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="arc-row">
        <dt>2025 — 2026</dt>
        <dd>Stock manager + internal tools developer, Suitsupply SF. Built the Daily Operations Platform from scratch.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="arc-row">
        <dt>2017</dt>
        <dd>A2 at Rock in Rio, 80,000 attendees a day.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="arc-row">
        <dt>2015 — 2022</dt>
        <dd>A1 / OPS coordinator, Vocal Livre (São Paulo). Toured Brazil at 100–25,000-attendee scale. Latin Grammy–nominated production team for the album <em>Temporal</em> (2023).</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="arc-row">
        <dt>2019 — 2020</dt>
        <dd>AudioVisual Operations at UNASP, São Paulo. Ran AV for 5,000+ weekly attendees and trained students on signal flow, console operation, and broadcast workflow.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="arc-row">
        <dt>2015 — 2019</dt>
        <dd>A1 + Assistant Producer, Novo Tom at UNASP — internship running sound for campus events and producing recordings.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="arc-row">
        <dt>2012 — 2014</dt>
        <dd>IT support and AV operations, Colégio Adventista IABC, Goiás, Brazil.</dd>
      </div>
    </dl>

    <h2 id="now">
      <span class="h2-tag">§ 02</span>
      <span class="h2-text">What I work on now.</span>
    </h2>

    <dl class="stack">
      <div class="stack-row">
        <dt>LIVE AUDIO</dt>
        <dd>FOH and monitor on Yamaha / DiGiCo / Avid, Dante-networked systems, Shure RF coordination.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="stack-row">
        <dt>SOFTWARE</dt>
        <dd>Node, Postgres, WebSockets, PWAs, MCP servers, the boring Linux deployment work that makes them stay up.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="stack-row">
        <dt>HARDWARE</dt>
        <dd><a href="/projects/shaddow">Shaddow</a>: 12 V automotive power and USB / CAN dock electronics in Flux.ai and KiCad.</dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </article>

  <figure class="photo full-bleed">
    <picture>
      <source type="image/webp" srcset="/images/about/sound-image-hoodie-1200.webp 1200w, /images/about/sound-image-hoodie-1600.webp 1600w" sizes="100vw" />
      <img src="/images/about/sound-image-hoodie-1200.jpg" srcset="/images/about/sound-image-hoodie-1200.jpg 1200w, /images/about/sound-image-hoodie-1600.jpg 1600w" sizes="100vw" alt="Victor in a Sound Image hoodie — backstage selfie before doors, gear cases visible behind him." width="1600" height="1067" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
    </picture>
    <figcaption><span class="fig">FIG. 04 ·</span> SOUND IMAGE · BACKSTAGE PORTRAIT · 2025</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <figure class="photo full-bleed">
    <picture>
      <source type="image/webp" srcset="/images/about/vo-booth-akg-rokit-1200.webp 1200w, /images/about/vo-booth-akg-rokit-1600.webp 1600w" sizes="100vw" />
      <img src="/images/about/vo-booth-akg-rokit-1200.jpg" srcset="/images/about/vo-booth-akg-rokit-1200.jpg 1200w, /images/about/vo-booth-akg-rokit-1600.jpg 1600w" sizes="100vw" alt="Voiceover booth — AKG large-diaphragm condenser on a boom, KRK Rokit monitors flanking the screen, acoustic treatment on the wall behind." width="1600" height="1067" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
    </picture>
    <figcaption><span class="fig">FIG. 05 ·</span> VO BOOTH · AKG + KRK ROKIT · ENGENHEIRO COELHO · 2020</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <figure class="photo full-bleed">
    <picture>
      <source type="image/webp" srcset="/images/about/keith-urban-soundimage-1200.webp 1200w, /images/about/keith-urban-soundimage-1600.webp 1600w" sizes="100vw" />
      <img src="/images/about/keith-urban-soundimage-1200.jpg" srcset="/images/about/keith-urban-soundimage-1200.jpg 1200w, /images/about/keith-urban-soundimage-1600.jpg 1600w" sizes="100vw" alt="Sound Image / Clair Global crew prepping black SOUND IMAGE flight cases and a Shure RF rig in a FIFA World Cup 2026 hospitality lounge, the tournament graphic glowing on the screens behind them." width="1600" height="1067" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
    </picture>
    <figcaption><span class="fig">FIG. 06 ·</span> SOUND IMAGE / CLAIR GLOBAL · FIFA WORLD CUP 2026 · LOAD-IN</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <article class="about-body">
    <h2 id="hire">
      <span class="h2-tag">§ 03</span>
      <span class="h2-text">Hire me.</span>
    </h2>
    <p>
      Open to AV engineering, full-stack, or operations + technology roles —
      San Francisco, hybrid, or remote.
    </p>
    <p class="pull-quote">
      Best fit is a team where the person running cable and the person writing
      the code are allowed to be the same person.
    </p>

    <ul class="contact-strip" aria-label="Contact channels">
      <li>
        <span class="contact-key">EMAIL</span>
        <a
          href="mailto:info@victorocha.com"
          aria-label="Email Joao V. Rocha at info@victorocha.com"
        >info@victorocha.com</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="contact-key">LINKEDIN</span>
        <a
          href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/victordorocha/"
          rel="me noopener"
          aria-label="LinkedIn profile — victordorocha"
        >linkedin.com/in/victordorocha</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="contact-key">GITHUB</span>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/joaovorocha"
          rel="me noopener"
          aria-label="GitHub profile — joaovorocha"
        >github.com/joaovorocha</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="contact-key">RÉSUMÉ</span>
        <a
          href="/resume"
          aria-label="Long-form résumé"
        >Long-form résumé</a>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="credentials">
      <span class="h2-tag">§ 04</span>
      <span class="h2-text">Languages, certs, schooling.</span>
    </h2>

    <dl class="creds">
      <div class="creds-row">
        <dt>LANG</dt>
        <dd>English &amp; Portuguese — native / bilingual. Spanish — elementary.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="creds-row">
        <dt>CERT</dt>
        <dd>Allen &amp; Heath dLive (May 2026) · Dante Level 1 (Apr 2026) · Shure Axient Digital / PSM · Networking for Audio Professionals.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="creds-row">
        <dt>EDU</dt>
        <dd>
          B.A. in Communication, Broadcasting Technology — UNASP, São Paulo, 2020.<br>
          Graduation thesis: <em>PodLer</em> — an immersive podcast on classic Brazilian literature. Highest score from the faculty panel.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>

    <h2 id="community">
      <span class="h2-tag">§ 05</span>
      <span class="h2-text">Community + service.</span>
    </h2>

    <dl class="stack">
      <div class="stack-row">
        <dt>2018 — 2019</dt>
        <dd>Student Liaison, Monterey Bay Academy, CA. Supported international students, maintained campus facilities, cross-cultural work that also built the English fluency now used every day on the job.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="stack-row">
        <dt>2016</dt>
        <dd>Volunteer, ADRA International. Helped build an elementary school in Nova Jerusalém, Amazonas, Brazil.</dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </article>

  <figure class="photo full-bleed">
    <picture>
      <source type="image/webp" srcset="/images/about/van-rear-doors-1200.webp 1200w, /images/about/van-rear-doors-1600.webp 1600w" sizes="100vw" />
      <img src="/images/about/van-rear-doors-1200.jpg" srcset="/images/about/van-rear-doors-1200.jpg 1200w, /images/about/van-rear-doors-1600.jpg 1600w" sizes="100vw" alt="Victor framed at the open rear doors of the van — interior buildout visible behind him, late-day light." width="1600" height="1067" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
    </picture>
    <figcaption><span class="fig">FIG. 07 ·</span> VAN · REAR DOORS · PORTRAIT · 2026</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <footer class="container">
    <p class="colophon">
      Built with Astro, hosted on Cloudflare Pages, written in markdown. Source at
      <a
        href="https://github.com/joaovorocha/victorocha.com"
        rel="noopener"
        aria-label="Source repository on GitHub — joaovorocha/victorocha.com"
      >github.com/joaovorocha/victorocha.com</a>.
    </p>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .portrait {
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0;
    max-width: 480px;
  }
  .portrait img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .page-head { margin: 3rem 0 var(--chapter); }
  .page-head h1 { margin: 0.5rem 0 1.5rem; }
  .page-head .lede {
    color: var(--console-ink);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
    max-width: 42ch;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .page-head .lede + .lede { margin-top: 0.75rem; }

  .jump-nav {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--console-rule);
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1.75rem;
    font-family: var(--f-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-micro);
    letter-spacing: var(--tr-micro);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .jump-nav a {
    color: var(--console-dim);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
    padding-bottom: 2px;
    transition: color 120ms ease, border-color 120ms ease;
  }
  .jump-nav a:hover,
  .jump-nav a:focus-visible {
    color: var(--console-ink);
    border-bottom-color: var(--console-ink);
    outline: none;
  }

  .about-body {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }
  .about-body + .about-body { margin-top: var(--chapter); }

  .about-body h2 {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 3.5rem 0 1.75rem;
    scroll-margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  .about-body h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .about-body h2 .h2-tag {
    font-family: var(--f-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-micro);
    letter-spacing: var(--tr-micro);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--console-dim);
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    padding-top: 0.35em;
  }
  .about-body h2 .h2-text { flex: 1 1 auto; }

  /* Mono key-value grids: arc, stack, creds */
  .arc, .stack, .creds {
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.85rem;
  }
  .arc-row, .stack-row, .creds-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(8.5rem, 11rem) 1fr;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--console-rule);
  }
  .arc-row:last-child,
  .stack-row:last-child,
  .creds-row:last-child {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--console-rule);
  }
  .arc dt, .stack dt, .creds dt {
    font-family: var(--f-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-micro);
    letter-spacing: var(--tr-micro);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--console-dim);
    padding-top: 0.25em;
  }
  .arc dd, .stack dd, .creds dd {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--console-ink);
  }

  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .arc-row, .stack-row, .creds-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.35rem;
    }
  }

  .pull-quote {
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--console-ink);
    background: var(--console-rule);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--console-ink);
  }

  .contact-strip {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 2rem 0 3rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--console-rule);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--console-rule);
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.85rem;
  }
  .contact-strip li {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(6.5rem, 8rem) 1fr;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    align-items: baseline;
  }
  .contact-strip .contact-key {
    font-family: var(--f-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-micro);
    letter-spacing: var(--tr-micro);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--console-dim);
  }
  .contact-strip a {
    color: var(--console-ink);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--console-rule);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    transition: border-color 120ms ease;
    word-break: break-word;
  }
  .contact-strip a:hover,
  .contact-strip a:focus-visible {
    border-bottom-color: var(--console-ink);
    outline: none;
  }

  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .contact-strip li {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.25rem;
    }
  }

  .colophon {
    font-family: var(--f-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-micro);
    letter-spacing: var(--tr-micro);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--console-dim);
    margin: var(--chapter) auto 3rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--console-rule);
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .colophon-ch { color: var(--console-ink); margin-right: 0.5em; }
  .colophon a {
    color: var(--console-dim);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--console-rule);
  }
  .colophon a:hover,
  .colophon a:focus-visible {
    color: var(--console-ink);
    border-bottom-color: var(--console-ink);
    outline: none;
  }

  /* Mobile — H1 sizing, body padding alignment with container, full-bleed reset, portrait cap */
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .page-head h1 {
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 9vw, 3rem);
      line-height: 1.05;
      overflow-wrap: break-word;
    }
    .page-head .lede { font-size: 1.125rem; max-width: 100%; }
    /* Align about-body's 2rem to container's 1.25rem mobile padding */
    .about-body { padding: 0 1.25rem; }
    .colophon { font-size: 0.7rem; padding-top: 1rem; }
    /* Reset desktop full-bleed margin that relies on --rail-w even when rail is hidden */
    figure.photo.full-bleed {
      margin-left: calc(50% - 50vw);
      margin-right: calc(50% - 50vw);
      max-width: 100vw;
    }
    /* Cap tall/portrait figures so they don't dominate the mobile fold */
    figure.photo.full-bleed img {
      max-height: 80vh;
      object-fit: cover;
    }
    .pull-quote { padding: 1rem 1.1rem; font-size: 1rem; }
    .about-body h2 { gap: 0.5rem; margin: 2.5rem 0 1.25rem; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 380px) {
    .page-head h1 { font-size: 1.75rem; }
    .page-head .lede { font-size: 1rem; }
  }
  /* Print — clean single column, no full-bleed, hide jump nav */
  @media print {
    .page-head, .about-body { max-width: 100%; padding: 0; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
    .jump-nav { display: none; }
    figure.photo.full-bleed {
      margin-left: 0;
      margin-right: 0;
      max-width: 100%;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }
    .pull-quote {
      background: none;
      border-left-color: #000;
      color: #000;
    }
    .contact-strip, .arc, .stack, .creds { page-break-inside: avoid; }
    .colophon { border-color: #000; color: #000; }
  }
</style>
